          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server designed to determine the borough of New York City based on a given input parameter. Scalar functions return a single value and are used for computations or transformations that can be expressed as a single value output."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
