      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Scalar functions can introduce performance overhead, especially when used in SELECT statements that process large datasets. This is because scalar functions are executed row-by-row, which can lead to slower query performance. To mitigate this, ensure that the function logic is optimized and consider using inline table-valued functions if performance becomes an issue."
